02/03/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU police agency Europol will soon sign an agreement with the countries of the western Balkans on fighting organised crime, the European Commission's Director General for Justice and Home Affairs, Adrian Fortescue, announced Thursday (27 February). Fortescue said preparatory talks with Croatia, Albania, Serbia-Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Macedonia are underway. (Tanjug - 28/02/03)
